a.xlink:title:
aind_data_schema.core.mri_session.MRIScan
Description of a 3D scan
Attributes: primary_scan (bool): Indicates the primary scan used for downstream analysis voxel_sizes (Optional[Scale3dTransform]): Resolution. Default is None.

aind_data_schema.models.coordinates.Rotation3dTransform
Values to be vector-added to a 3D position. Often needed to specify a device or tile's origin.

aind_data_schema.models.coordinates.Scale3dTransform
Values to be vector-multiplied with a 3D position, equivalent to the diagonals of a 3x3 transform matrix. Represents voxel spacing if used as the first applied coordinate transform.

aind_data_schema.models.coordinates.Translation3dTransform
Values to be vector-added to a 3D position. Often needed to specify a device or tile's origin.

aind_data_schema.core.mri_session.MriSession
Description of an MRI scan
Attributes: subject_id (str): Unique identifier for the subject. If this is not a Allen LAS ID, indicate this in the Notes. experimenter_full_name (List[str]): First and last name of the experimenter(s). protocol_id (str): DOI for protocols.io animal_weight_prior (Optional[Decimal]): Animal weight before procedure. Default is None. animal_weight_post (Optional[Decimal]): Animal weight after procedure. Default is None.

aind_data_schema.models.devices.Scanner
Description of a MRI Scanner
Attributes: path_to_cad (Optional[str]): For CUSTOM manufactured devices. Default is None.
